                  </hi>.—<hi rend="italic">He was further charged with having been convicted in July</hi>, 1861, <hi rend="italic">in the name of Donkin, to which he</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">PLEADED GUILTY</hi>—<hi rend="italic">
